{"event_id":8,"timestamp_ns":3213170,"kind":{"type":"SourceCode","source":"## Tests for self-referential function declarations\n## These test that functions can reference themselves during their own declaration\n\n## Basic self-referential function with explicit return type\nfunc identity(i: int) :: int { {i} }\nprint :identity(identity(42))\n\n## Nested calls to self-referential function\nfunc pass_through(x: int) :: int { {x} }\nprint :pass_through(pass_through(pass_through(7)))\n\n## Self-referential function used in expression context\nfunc echo(n: int) :: int { {n} }\nlet result = echo(echo(echo(3)));\nprint :result\n\n#*@stdout\n42\n7\n3\n*#\n","filename":"./tests/lang/basic/self_referential_function.tl"}}
